ISLAMABAD, Aug 05 (APP): Minister of State for Information and Broadcasting Farrukh Habib on Thursday asked the Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) supremo Nawaz Sharif to quit his arrogance and come back Pakistan to complete his sentence as the British government had rejected his visa extension plea.
In a tweet, he said Nawaz Sharif who was convicted of corruption and declared as absconder by the court had been living as fugitive in the United Kingdom on expired visa.
